verbose_text: A recent study showed that genetic ablation of the mitochondrial complex III components Rieske iron-sulfur protein (RISP, encoded by Uqcrfs1) and ubiquinone binding protein (QPC, encoded by Uqcrq) in Tregs affects mitochondrial respiration, leading to defective Treg function.
